sec.p:
The synthesis of polymers from renewable resources has been investigated by leading research teams from different countries.3,4 These studies have been initiated by a search for alternative raw materials, replacing the petrochemical resources running short. Investigations in the field of polyurethanes (PU) are especially active. Interest in the use of renewable raw materials, in particular, vegetable oils for preparing PUR foams is increasing, which has the following reasons:


petroleum resources are getting short rapidly, and their products become increasingly expensive;

polyols from vegetable oils are competitive with petro-chemical polyols in terms of price;

the use of vegetable polyols in PUR compositions makes it possible to improve the properties of some prepared foams, especially their hydrophobicity.
